21/01/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A bomb threat closed Sofia's international airport for more than an hour on Sunday (January 20th), which delayed flights. 
An unidentified woman called police around noon saying an explosive device was in the old terminal. 
Police evacuated and searched the facility, but then resumed normal operations after finding no suspicious items. 
(Darik, Xinhua, UPI, Actualno, Reuters, Focus - 20/01/08)
